properties.Name: TermLifeInsurance
properties.Description:
Term life insurance is the simplest type of life insurance offered.

Term life insurance provides life insurance protection for a specified period (or term) and pays a benefit only if the insured dies during that period.

Includes:
- Increasing Term
- Level Term
- Decreasing Term

where:
Increasing Term:
Term life insurance in which the death benefit increases periodically over the term of the policy.  It is frequently purchased as a cost of living rider to a whole life policy.

Level Term:
A type of term life insurance policy in which the face value remains constant from the effective date until the expiration date.

Decreasing Term:
A type of life insurance that provides a declining death benefit throughout the term of the contract and finally reaches zero at the end of the term.
